@page "/sms-consent"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@layout PublicDocumentLayout
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>SMS Consent - PTDoc</PageTitle>

<article class="public-policy-page" aria-labelledby="sms-consent-title">
    <header class="public-policy-page__hero">
        <p class="public-policy-page__eyebrow">SMS Consent</p>
        <h1 id="sms-consent-title">PTDoc SMS Consent and Text Messaging Terms</h1>
        <p>
            PTDoc sends transactional text messages for secure patient intake, account verification,
            appointment-related reminders, and care-related follow-up for participating physical
            therapy clinics.
        </p>
    </header>

    <section class="public-policy-page__section" aria-labelledby="sms-program-title">
        <h2 id="sms-program-title">What Messages We Send</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>One-time verification codes for secure patient intake access.</li>
            <li>Secure intake invitations and reminders to complete intake before a visit.</li>
            <li>Appointment-related reminders or care-team follow-up when enabled by the clinic.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            PTDoc does not use this SMS program for marketing, lead generation, promotional offers,
            financial services, or unrelated third-party messaging.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="public-policy-page__section" aria-labelledby="sms-opt-in-title">
        <h2 id="sms-opt-in-title">How Patients Opt In</h2>
        <p>
            A clinic sends the patient a secure intake invitation link. The patient opens that link,
            selects <strong>Text Message</strong>, enters the mobile number associated with their
            patient record, and clicks <strong>Send Code</strong> to receive a one-time verification
            code. During intake review, patients may also confirm SMS communication consent for
            care-related reminders and follow-up.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="public-policy-page__section" aria-labelledby="sms-rates-title">
        <h2 id="sms-rates-title">Message Frequency, Rates, and Opt Out</h2>
        <p>
            Message frequency varies based on clinic workflows and patient activity. Message and
            data rates may apply. Reply <strong>STOP</strong> to opt out of SMS messages. Reply
            <strong>HELP</strong> for help.
        </p>
        <p>
            If you opt out, PTDoc may still provide essential healthcare information through your
            clinic or another permitted communication channel.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="public-policy-page__section" aria-labelledby="sms-examples-title">
        <h2 id="sms-examples-title">Example Messages</h2>
        <div class="public-policy-page__examples">
            <p>PTDoc verification code: 123456. This code expires in 10 minutes. Reply STOP to opt out.</p>
            <p>PTDoc: Your clinic has sent you a secure intake form. Please complete it before your visit. Reply STOP to opt out.</p>
            <p>PTDoc: Reminder from your physical therapy care team. Please review your intake or appointment information. Reply STOP to opt out.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="public-policy-page__section" aria-labelledby="sms-links-title">
        <h2 id="sms-links-title">Related Policies</h2>
        <p>
            Review the <a href="/privacy">PTDoc Privacy Policy</a> and
            <a href="/terms">PTDoc Terms and Conditions</a> for more information.
        </p>
    </section>
</article>
